/wiki/Holnon: Holnon  is a commune in the Aisne department in Hauts-de-France in northern France.
/wiki/Jaulgonne: Jaulgonne  is a commune in the Aisne department and Hauts-de-France region of northern France.
/wiki/Ch%C3%A2teau-Thierry: Château-Thierry (French: [ʃato tjeʁi]) is a French commune situated in the department of the Aisne, in the administrative region of Hauts-de-France and in the historic Province of Champagne.
/wiki/Laon: Laon (French pronunciation: ​[lɑ̃]) is the capital city of the Aisne department in Hauts-de-France, northern France. As of 2012[update] its population was 25,317.
/wiki/Marcel_Gaumont: Marcel Gaumont was a French sculptor born on 27 January 1880 in Tours.  He died in Paris on 20 November 1962.
/wiki/M%C3%A9zi%C3%A8res-sur-Oise: Mézières-sur-Oise  is a commune in the Aisne department in Hauts-de-France in northern France.
/wiki/Charles_Desvergnes: Charles Desvergnes (1860–1928) was a French sculptor.
/wiki/Montaigu,_Aisne: Montaigu is a commune in the Aisne department in Hauts-de-France in northern France.
/wiki/Origny-Sainte-Benoite: Origny-Sainte-Benoite  is a commune in the Aisne department in Hauts-de-France in northern France.
/wiki/Appilly: Appilly  is a commune in the Oise department in northern France.
/wiki/Pontavert: Pontavert  is a commune in the Aisne department in Hauts-de-France in northern France.
/wiki/Saint-Quentin,_Aisne: Saint-Quentin (French pronunciation: ​[sɛ̃kɑ̃tɛ̃]; Picard: Saint-Kintin) is a commune in the Aisne department in Hauts-de-France in northern France. It has been identified as the Augusta Veromanduorum of antiquity.  It is named after Saint Quentin, who is said to have been martyred there in the 3rd century.
/wiki/Paul_Bigot: Paul Bigot (20 October 1870 – 8 June 1942) was a French architect.
/wiki/Henri_Bouchard: Henri Bouchard (13 December 1875 – 30 November 1960), was a French sculptor.
/wiki/Paul_Landowski: Paul Maximilien Landowski (1 June 1875 – 31 March 1961) was a French monument sculptor of Polish descent. His best-known work is Christ the Redeemer in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil.
